{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018BCzLekpGiDoweMavG5bH8","type":"tool_result","content":"# mongodb/external-access-horizons\n# MongoDB external-access-horizons task\n\nparams:\n  cluster_prefix:\n    default: mongo-rs\n    description: StatefulSet name of the replica set members.\n  replica_set_name:\n    default: rs0\n    description: MongoDB replica set _id used when initiating the set.\n  client_pod_name:\n    default: mongo-client\n    description: External client pod used to reach the advertised endpoints.\n  mongo_client_image:\n    default: mongo:6.0\n    description: Container image used for the mongo client pod.\n  external_host_prefix:\n    default: domain-rs\n    description: Prefix of the external split-horizon hostnames.\n  nodeport_start:\n    default: 31181\n    description: First NodePort assigned to the externally exposed members.\n\nprompt: |\n  A 3-member MongoDB replica set is running in the mongodb namespace.\n  Each member is exposed via NodePort with external hostnames:\n\n  - {{params.external_host_prefix}}-1:{{params.nodeport_start}}\n  - {{params.external_host_prefix}}-2:31182\n  - {{params.external_host_prefix}}-3:31183\n\n  A {{params.client_pod_name}} pod is available with those hostnames mapped to a node IP.\n\n  Task:\n  - Configure the replica set to advertise the external endpoints (split-horizon).\n  - Do not change the NodePort services.\n\nnamespace_contract:\n  required_roles: []\n\nmetrics:\n  - time_to_first_mutation\n\npreconditionUnits:\n  - name: mongo_env_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      # AUTHORITATIVE skip-if-running probe (P32): succeed when the canonical\n      # StatefulSet exists OR any pod is Running, so the destructive namespace\n      # rebuild below is skipped on an inherited cluster even if its pods are\n      # momentarily not Running (mid-restart from a prior stage) -- the\n      # StatefulSet persists across that window. The bare `grep -c Running`\n      # could miss such a cluster and clobber inherited state.\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb get statefulset {{params.cluster_prefix}} >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n mongodb get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -q Running'\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n    apply:\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c '\n          kubectl delete namespace mongodb --ignore-not-found=true; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/mongodb --timeout=120s || true\n          '\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl create namespace mongodb\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/external-access-horizons/resource/services.yaml\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/external-access-horizons/resource/statefulset.yaml\"\n        sleep: 5\n      - command: |\n          for i in $(seq 1 60); do\n            ready=$(kubectl -n mongodb get sts {{params.cluster_prefix}} -o jsonpath='{.status.readyReplicas}' 2>/dev/null)\n            if [ \"${ready:-0}\" -ge 3 ]; then\n              exit 0\n            fi\n            sleep 5\n          done\n          exit 1\n        sleep: 2\n      # Pod-Ready != mongod accepting TCP (§1.10): ping-until-ok before rs.initiate.\n      - command: |\n          for i in $(seq 1 30); do\n            kubectl -n mongodb exec mongo-rs-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval 'db.runCommand({ping:1}).ok' 2>/dev/null | grep -q 1 && exit 0\n            sleep 3\n          done\n          exit 1\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: |\n          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongo-rs-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\n          rs.initiate({_id:\"{{params.replica_set_name}}\",members:[\n            {_id:0,host:\"mongo-rs-0.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"},\n            {_id:1,host:\"mongo-rs-1.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"},\n            {_id:2,host:\"mongo-rs-2.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"}\n          ]})'\n        sleep: 5\n      - command: |\n          for i in $(seq 1 20); do\n            kubectl -n mongodb exec mongo-rs-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval 'db.hello().isWritablePrimary' | grep true && exit 0\n            sleep 3\n          done\n          exit 1\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: |\n          node_ip=$(kubectl get nodes -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.metadata.name}{\" \"}{range .status.addresses[?(@.type==\"InternalIP\")]}{.address}{\"\\n\"}{end}{end}' | awk '$1 !~ /control-plane|master/ {print $2; exit}')\n          if [ -z \"$node_ip\" ]; then\n            # Single-node cluster (only the control-plane node, e.g. default\n            # kind): fall back to its InternalIP instead of failing.\n            node_ip=$(kubectl get nodes -o jsonpath='{.items[0].status.addresses[?(@.type==\"InternalIP\")].address}')\n          fi\n          if [ -z \"$node_ip\" ]; then\n            exit 1\n          fi\n          cat <<EOF | kubectl -n mongodb apply -f -\n          apiVersion: v1\n          kind: Pod\n          metadata:\n            name: {{params.client_pod_name}}\n          spec:\n            restartPolicy: Never\n            hostAliases:\n            - ip: \"$node_ip\"\n              hostnames:\n              - {{params.external_host_prefix}}-1\n              - {{params.external_host_prefix}}-2\n              - {{params.external_host_prefix}}-3\n            containers:\n            - name: mongosh\n              image: {{params.mongo_client_image}}\n              command: [\"sleep\", \"3600\"]\n          EOF\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb wait --for=condition=ready pod {{params.client_pod_name}} --timeout=300s\"\n        sleep: 2\n    verify:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n\n  # Self-contained external access (composition safety): the prompt states the NodePort\n  # services + client pod ALREADY exist (\"Do not change the NodePort services\"); the\n  # agent only configures split-horizon rs.conf. mongo_env_ready seeds those on its\n  # destructive build path, which is SKIPPED on an inherited cluster, so the\n  # mongo-external-* services and the client pod are absent -> the oracle's service\n  # check fails and the agent has no endpoints to advertise. Re-establish them\n  # additively when the services are missing: apply the NodePort services and recreate\n  # the node-IP-mapped client pod. Never deletes the namespace or the running cluster.\n  # Standalone they already exist so the probe matches and this unit skips.\n  - name: external_access_fixture\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb get svc mongo-external-1\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n    apply:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/external-access-horizons/resource/services.yaml\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: |\n          node_ip=$(kubectl get nodes -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.metadata.name}{\" \"}{range .status.addresses[?(@.type==\"InternalIP\")]}{.address}{\"\\n\"}{end}{end}' | awk '$1 !~ /control-plane|master/ {print $2; exit}')\n          if [ -z \"$node_ip\" ]; then\n            node_ip=$(kubectl get nodes -o jsonpath='{.items[0].status.addresses[?(@.type==\"InternalIP\")].address}')\n          fi\n          if [ -z \"$node_ip\" ]; then\n            exit 0\n          fi\n          kubectl -n mongodb get pod {{params.client_pod_name}} >/dev/null 2>&1 || cat <<EOF | kubectl -n mongodb apply -f -\n          apiVersion: v1\n          kind: Pod\n          metadata:\n            name: {{params.client_pod_name}}\n          spec:\n            restartPolicy: Never\n            hostAliases:\n            - ip: \"$node_ip\"\n              hostnames:\n              - {{params.external_host_prefix}}-1\n              - {{params.external_host_prefix}}-2\n              - {{params.external_host_prefix}}-3\n            containers:\n            - name: mongosh\n              image: {{params.mongo_client_image}}\n              command: [\"sleep\", \"3600\"]\n          EOF\n        sleep: 2\n    verify:\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb get svc mongo-external-1 >/dev/null 2>&1; true'\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n\noracle:\n  verify:\n    commands:\n      - command: \"python3 cases/mongodb/external-access-horizons/oracle/oracle.py\"\n        timeout_sec: 120","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"471dcb56-fd46-44ae-af17-58cc4f3c6001","uuid":"c7958fdb-1ec9-4fbf-a01b-7902a4bf0e24","timestamp":"2026-07-03T11:38:14.978Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"# mongodb/external-access-horizons\n# MongoDB external-access-horizons task\n\nparams:\n  cluster_prefix:\n    default: mongo-rs\n    description: StatefulSet name of the replica set members.\n  replica_set_name:\n    default: rs0\n    description: MongoDB replica set _id used when initiating the set.\n  client_pod_name:\n    default: mongo-client\n    description: External client pod used to reach the advertised endpoints.\n  mongo_client_image:\n    default: mongo:6.0\n    description: Container image used for the mongo client pod.\n  external_host_prefix:\n    default: domain-rs\n    description: Prefix of the external split-horizon hostnames.\n  nodeport_start:\n    default: 31181\n    description: First NodePort assigned to the externally exposed members.\n\nprompt: |\n  A 3-member MongoDB replica set is running in the mongodb namespace.\n  Each member is exposed via NodePort with external hostnames:\n\n  - {{params.external_host_prefix}}-1:{{params.nodeport_start}}\n  - {{params.external_host_prefix}}-2:31182\n  - {{params.external_host_prefix}}-3:31183\n\n  A {{params.client_pod_name}} pod is available with those hostnames mapped to a node IP.\n\n  Task:\n  - Configure the replica set to advertise the external endpoints (split-horizon).\n  - Do not change the NodePort services.\n\nnamespace_contract:\n  required_roles: []\n\nmetrics:\n  - time_to_first_mutation\n\npreconditionUnits:\n  - name: mongo_env_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      #